oai_dc:dc.dc:title: EXPOSURE RESEARCH ON CONCRETE IN SEA WATER
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Cook, Herbert K.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: concrete design
concrete durability
coastal structures
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Many coastal installations are constructed entirely of concrete or contain concrete in a large part of the structure, particularly those portions which are submerged, and those portions between low and high water. It is the latter locations which are submitted to the most severe exposure.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 3 (1952): Proceedings of Third Conference on Coastal Engineering, Cambridge, Massachusetts, 1952.; 18
